                     <interp inst="def1-851-18470301" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">JOHN BARNARD</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18470301-851-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18470301-851-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18470301-851-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="stealingFromMaster"></interp>for stealing 14 quarts of beans, value 3<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., the goods of <persName id="t18470301-name-1163" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18470301-name-1163" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470301-name-1163" type="surname" value="HARVEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470301-name-1163" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18470301-851-offence-1 t18470301-name-1163"></join>James Harvey</persName>, his master.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18470301-name-1164" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18470301-name-1164" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470301-name-1164" type="surname" value="REED"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470301-name-1164" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM REED</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable V</hi> 18.) Between six and seven o'clock on the evening of the 5th Feb. I was at St. Ann's-hill, Wandsworth, and saw the prisoner—he had a bag, containing some beans, under his arm—I stopped him, and asked him what he had got there—he said, "Some corn"—I asked where he was going to take it—he said, "To a friend"—I asked if his master was aware he was going to take it—he said, "No"—I took him back to Mr. Harvey, who asked how he came to take these beans—he said, "Out of bravado,</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184703010183"></xptr>
               <p>to see if I could carry them so far without being stopped by the police"—Mr. Harvey said it was very wrong in him to take them away—he said he had taken them from the bin out of the other beans—there were fourteen quarts of them—I produce a sample of them, and a sample of beans from the stable.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18470301-name-1165" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18470301-name-1165" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470301-name-1165" type="surname" value="HARVEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470301-name-1165" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES HARVEY</persName>
                  </hi>. The prisoner had been in my employ for twelve months—I had no complaint of him—he had no authority to take these beans—a better servant no man could have—I would have no hesitation in taking him again.</p>
               <p>
